Uses of Package
net.sf.JRecord.Common

  • Packages that use net.sf.JRecord.Common 
    Package Description
    net.sf.JRecord.ByteIO
    This package holds low level Record-Oriented IO routines (reading / writing an Array of Bytes).
    net.sf.JRecord.Common
    This package holds Common code used in multiple JRecord packages.
    net.sf.JRecord.CsvParser
    This package holds Various CSV line parsers - classes to break a line into the fields using a field-Seperator String
    net.sf.JRecord.Details
    This package holds Classes that describe a Files Structure RecordLayout + the lines (Line, XmlLine) in the File.
    net.sf.JRecord.Details.fieldValue  
    net.sf.JRecord.External
    This package holds classes that convert Record-Layouts (copybooks) between external Files and the internal representation.
    net.sf.JRecord.IO
    This package holds all Record-Oriented IO routines.
    net.sf.JRecord.Numeric
    This package is contains code to Convert a Cobol Definition into a RecordEditor/JRecord Type.
    net.sf.JRecord.Types
    This package holds Type-Definitions plus the TypeManager that is a repositry for all the Types.
    net.sf.JRecord.schema  
    net.sf.JRecord.utilityClasses
